esetzesbegriff einen Referenzrahmen eigener Art, dessen unterschiedliche, Theologie, Philosophie, Rechtslehre und Geschichte umspannende Fragestellungen im Zentrum des Bandes stehen. Hier liegen die Wurzeln für unser modernes Rechtsverständnis wie auch die Gründe für die aktuell zum Vorschein tretenden Differenzen zwischen den Kulturkreisen und Religionen.  aThis volume examines how the notion of law was transformed and reformulated during the Middle Ages. It focuses on encounters between ancient and local legal traditions and the three great revelation religions – Judaism, Christianity, and Islam – each of which understood the written word of God as law and formulated new cultures. The work thus furnishes interdisciplinary and intercultural insight into medieval legal discourse.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLawxHistory. 0aLawxPhilosophy. 0aLaw, Medieval. 4aMittelalter. 4aPhilosophie. 4aRecht. 4aReligion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Medieval.2bisacsh  aLaw, philosophy, Middle Ages, religion.1 aBasse, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBláhová, Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrague, Rémi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurger, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampanini, Saverio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEusterschulte, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffel, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuldentops, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuldentops, Guy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarkins, Franklin T., eco